[center][size=6][color=#ffff00][b]Clothing Sets Checklist[/b][/color][/size]
[size=4]An in-game UI checklist to track [i]almost [/i]all unique clothing sets.[/size][/center]

Inspired by my [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/25594]Perk Shard Checklist[/url] and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/25755]Relic Terminal Checklist[/url] mods

This mod adds a simple, in-game UI to track [i]almost[/i] all unique clothing sets so you never have to alt-tab again.

[center][/center][img]https://i.imgur.com/uw4vHhK.gif[/img]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]New in 2.0.0[/b][/color][/size]
[color=#e06666][b]0-Engine is a new required dependency.[/b][/color] The mod will not run without it. See [b]Requirements[/b] below.
[list]
[*][b]Rebuilt Proximity Scanner:[/b] The scanner now reacts the moment you cross into range instead of polling on a timer. No CPU cost when you are away from any item, and tighter detection up close.
[*][b]Fixed:[/b] Johnny's Shoes and Johnny's Pants no longer trigger the scanner before those items are actually accessible.
[*][b]Removed:[/b] the scanner interval setting. The new system has no polling interval, so it no longer applies.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Features[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]An in-game UI checklist that automatically tracks clothing sets as you collect them.
[*]Progress is saved automatically with your game save (per-character).
[*]A [b]Settings[/b] tab to configure the Proximity Scanner range and optional [b]Lazy Mode[/b].
[*]In-game directions, closest fast travel points, and location info for every piece of clothing.
[*]A [b]Set Pin[/b] button to create a waypoint to the item's location.
[*]A [b]Teleport[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to instantly teleport to the item.
[*]A [b]Give Item[/b] button in case you're feeling extra lazy (or sold/salvaged the item).
[*]An [b]Unstuck[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to teleport you to V's H10 apartment if you get stuck due to a teleportation mishap.
[*]Counters to keep track of how many items/sets you've collected.
[/list]
I decided not to include the life path clothing sets or epilogue clothing sets. Aside from those, I should have most of the sets from the game covered. If there is anything I've missed, let me know.

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]How to Use[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Open the Cyber Engine Tweaks overlay.
[*]The [b]Clothing Sets Checklist[/b] window will appear.
[*]Click the sets tabs and items to get information on how to obtain the items.
[*][b]Automatic Tracking[/b]: Progress is automatically saved by checking your Wardrobe. If you have already collected some items, they will show up instantly.
[*][b]Proximity Scanning[/b]: Enable (default) this in the [b]Settings[/b] tab to see nearby items on your HUD as you play. 
[list][*]You can adjust the detection range in the [b]Settings[/b] tab (default 50m, adjustable from 25m to 100m). The scanner is event driven, so there is no scan interval to configure.
[/list][/list][*]To save your character's progress, [b]Quicksave (F5)[/b] or [b]Manual Save[/b] your game. The progress is tied to that save file.
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Lazy Mode[/b][/color][/size]
For those who just want to get it done, you can enable [b]Lazy Mode[/b] in the Settings tab. This will show the [b]Teleport,[/b] [b]Give Item[/b], and [b]Unstuck[/b] buttons.

[color=#e06666][b]WARNING:[/b][/color] Using teleport functions can be risky. It may cause issues with your save or get you stuck. Use at your own risk and always have a recent manual save!

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Requirements[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/107]Cyber Engine Tweaks[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/27967]0-Engine[/url] (pure CET-only build). [color=#e06666][b]New required dependency for 2.0.0.[/b][/color] It has its own requirements, listed on its mod page.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Installation[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/27967]0-Engine[/url] and its requirements (see [b]Requirements[/b] above).
[*]Install with a mod manager (recommended).
[*]For manual install, download and extract the main file into your Cyberpunk 2077 game directory.
[/list][line]
[b][color=#ffff00][size=4]Click to view the full list of Clothing Sets included
[/size][/color][/b]Most of the set info came from [url=https://cyberpunk.fandom.com/wiki/Cyberpunk_2077_Cosmetic_Sets]Cyberpunk 2077 Cosmetic Sets[/url] and various fragmented sources on the internet. Most of which is out of date as of patch 2.0. So, this mod required a lot of running around in-game, finding the locations, and writing down directions. I have created an article that lists all the sets, their locations and directions from the mod [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/articles/2284/]here[/url].

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Reccomendations[/b][/color][/size]
This mod pairs fantastically with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/8103]Set Bonuses[/url] by [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/users/4211422]apart[/url]. [size=1][i]Recent updates to that mod made me get off my butt and finally finish this one![/i][/size]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Known Issues[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]When you use the "Set Map Pin" button, the breadcrumbs (navigation path) may not appear immediately. You will need to [b]open and close your in-game Map (M)[/b] for the path to appear.
[/list]
[line]
